    question: 'Some people think that technology has made our lives more complex, while others believe that it has simplified them. Discuss both views and give your opinion.',
    modelAnswer: 'In recent decades, technological advancements have fundamentally transformed human existence, sparking profound debate about their overall impact. While critics contend that modern innovations have complicated our lives, I firmly believe that technology has significantly simplified human activity when utilized judiciously.\n\nOn one hand, technology undeniably introduces new complexities. The perpetual influx of information through smartphones and social media creates cognitive overload, fragmenting attention spans and eroding deep concentration. Continuous digital connectivity blurs the boundaries between work and personal life, extending working hours and increasing stress levels. Moreover, rapid technological obsolescence necessitates constant learning, placing considerable cognitive demands on individuals across all age groups. For example, mastering new software or navigating updated digital platforms can be bewildering for those less technologically inclined.\n\nConversely, technology has revolutionized daily efficiency and accessibility. Communication has become instantaneous and global, transcending geographical barriers through video conferencing and messaging applications. Routine tasks from banking to grocery shopping have been automated, saving countless hours that can be redirected toward more meaningful pursuits. Education has been democratized, with online courses and digital libraries making knowledge accessible to anyone with internet access. Medical technology has also advanced exponentially, improving diagnostic accuracy and treatment outcomes worldwide.\n\nIn conclusion, while technology presents certain complexities, its transformative benefits in simplifying human life are overwhelming. The key lies in mindful utilization—establishing digital boundaries while embracing the conveniences that enhance our quality of life.',
    modelAnswerCN: '近几十年来，技术进步从根本上改变了人类的生活方式，引发了关于其整体影响的深刻辩论。虽然批评者认为现代创新使我们的生活变得复杂，但我坚信，如果明智地加以利用，技术已大大简化了人类活动。\n\n一方面，技术确实带来了新的复杂性。通过智能手机和社交媒体不断涌入的信息造成了认知过载，分散了注意力，削弱了深度集中能力。持续的数字连接模糊了工作与个人生活之间的界限，延长了工作时间，增加了压力水平。此外，技术的快速淘汰需要不断学习，对所有年龄段的人都造成了相当大的认知负担。例如，掌握新软件或浏览更新后的数字平台对于那些不太精通技术的人来说可能会令人困惑。\n\n相反，技术彻底改变了日常效率和可及性。通信变得即时且全球化，通过视频会议和消息应用程序突破了地理障碍。从银行业务到杂货店购物等日常任务已实现自动化，节省了无数小时，可以重新用于更有意义的追求。教育已经民主化，在线课程和数字图书馆使任何有互联网访问权限的人都能获得知识。医疗技术也取得了指数级进步，提高了全球的诊断准确性和治疗效果。\n\n总之，虽然技术带来了某些复杂性，但其在简化人类生活方面的变革性好处是压倒性的。关键在于明智的利用——在建立数字边界的同时，拥抱那些提高我们生活质量的便利设施。',
