    type: 'discuss both views',
    topic: 'Education',
    question: 'Some people believe that universities should focus on providing practical skills for students\' future careers, while others argue that the primary purpose of universities is to promote academic research. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.',
    modelAnswer: 'The fundamental purpose of higher education remains a subject of vigorous academic and societal discourse. While vocational training proponents emphasize career preparation, research advocates stress knowledge advancement. I contend that universities must balance both imperatives, as practical expertise and academic inquiry are mutually reinforcing pillars of excellence.\n\nAdvocates for practical skills argue that universities bear a responsibility to prepare students for competitive employment markets. In an era of rapid economic transformation, graduates require specialized technical competencies and industry experience to secure meaningful careers. Engineering programs, for instance, incorporate internships and project-based learning that simulate professional environments, ensuring graduates possess immediately applicable skills. This approach not only enhances employability but also ensures educational relevance to evolving workforce needs.\n\nConversely, research-oriented institutions maintain that universities serve as crucibles for human knowledge advancement. Groundbreaking discoveries in science, medicine, and humanities have historically emerged from university laboratories and libraries. Research-intensive environments cultivate critical thinking, intellectual curiosity, and innovation—qualities that benefit individuals and societies alike. Moreover, academic research drives economic development through technological innovation and knowledge transfer.\n\nIn my considered opinion, universities must synthesize practical training and academic research. While career preparation is vital, fostering a culture of inquiry is equally essential for long-term societal progress. The most effective educational models integrate theoretical knowledge with practical application, producing graduates who are not only employable but also capable of driving innovation.',
    modelAnswerCN: '高等教育的根本目的仍然是学术和社会激烈辩论的主题。虽然职业培训的支持者强调职业准备，但研究倡导者强调知识进步。我认为大学必须平衡这两个必要条件，因为实践专业知识和学术探究是卓越的相互支撑的支柱。\n\n实用技能的倡导者认为，大学有责任为学生准备竞争激烈的就业市场。在经济快速转型的时代，毕业生需要专门的技术能力和行业经验来获得有意义的职业。例如，工程项目包含实习和基于项目的学习，模拟专业环境，确保毕业生具备立即可用的技能。这种方法不仅提高了就业能力，还确保了教育与不断变化的劳动力需求的相关性。\n\n相反，研究型机构坚持认为大学是人类知识进步的熔炉。历史上，科学、医学和人文学科的突破性发现都来自大学实验室和图书馆。研究密集型环境培养批判性思维、求知欲和创新——这些品质对个人和社会都有利。此外，学术研究通过技术创新和知识转移推动经济发展。\n\n在我深思熟虑的观点中，大学必须综合实践培训和学术研究。虽然职业准备至关重要，但培养探究文化对于长期社会进步同样至关重要。最有效的教育模式将理论知识与实际应用相结合，培养出不仅有就业能力，而且能够推动创新的毕业生。',
    bandScore: 'Band 8.5',
