    type: 'discuss both views',
    topic: 'Media',
    question: 'Some people believe that traditional media (newspapers, TV) is still more reliable than social media, while others argue that social media provides more up-to-date information. Discuss both views and give your opinion.',
    modelAnswer: 'The evolving media landscape presents a complex choice between traditional outlets and social platforms, each offering distinct advantages in reliability and timeliness. Navigating this ecosystem requires discerning evaluation of information quality across both formats.\n\nTraditional media maintains established standards of journalistic integrity through rigorous editorial processes. Newspapers and television networks employ professional journalists who adhere to ethical guidelines, conduct thorough fact-checking, and provide contextual analysis. This institutional framework fosters accountability and reduces misinformation risks. Traditional media excels at in-depth reporting, offering comprehensive coverage that helps audiences understand multifaceted issues beyond surface-level headlines.\n\nSocial media revolutionizes information dissemination through real-time updates and democratized content sharing. Platforms enable instant access to breaking news from diverse sources, often before traditional media can report. Social media amplifies marginalized voices and grassroots perspectives, fostering a more inclusive public discourse. However, this speed comes with trade-offs: limited fact-checking, algorithmic bias, and viral misinformation can compromise reliability.\n\nIn my considered view, both media types serve complementary roles. Traditional media provides authoritative depth, while social media offers immediacy and diversity. The solution lies in media literacy—teaching audiences to cross-reference sources, verify claims, and critically evaluate information. By integrating insights from both formats, individuals can develop a more comprehensive understanding of current events.',
    modelAnswerCN: '不断发展的媒体格局在传统媒体和社交平台之间提供了复杂的选择，每种形式在可靠性和时效性方面都具有独特的优势。在这个生态系统中导航需要对两种格式的信息质量进行敏锐的评估。\n\n传统媒体通过严格的编辑流程维持既定的新闻诚信标准。报纸和电视网络聘请专业记者，他们遵守道德准则，进行彻底的事实核查，并提供背景分析。这种制度框架促进问责制并降低错误信息风险。传统媒体擅长深度报道，提供全面的报道，帮助受众理解超越表面标题的多方面问题。\n\n社交媒体通过实时更新和民主化的内容分享彻底改变了信息传播。平台支持即时访问来自不同来源的突发新闻，通常在传统媒体报道之前。社交媒体放大了边缘化声音和基层观点，促进了更具包容性的公共话语。然而，这种速度伴随着权衡：有限的事实核查、算法偏见和病毒式错误信息可能会影响可靠性。\n\n在我深思熟虑的观点中，两种媒体类型都发挥着互补作用。传统媒体提供权威性深度，而社交媒体提供即时性和多样性。解决方案在于媒体素养——教导受众交叉参考来源、验证主张并批判性地评估信息。通过整合两种格式的见解，个人可以更全面地了解时事。',
