    topic: 'Sports',
    question: 'Some people think that competitive sports are harmful to children, while others believe that they provide valuable life lessons. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.',
    modelAnswer: 'Competitive sports occupy a complex position in childhood development, offering potential benefits alongside significant risks that require careful management by coaches, parents, and educators.\n\nCritics highlight several valid concerns about competitive sports for children. The win-at-all-costs mentality can create excessive pressure, contributing to anxiety, performance stress, and even burnout. Physical injuries remain a constant risk, particularly in high-contact sports like football or gymnastics. Overemphasis on competition may foster unhealthy comparison and diminish the intrinsic joy of physical activity, potentially turning children away from sports entirely. Furthermore, unequal access to resources and coaching can exacerbate social disparities in youth sports participation.\n\nProponents emphasize the transformative life lessons competitive sports can impart. Team sports cultivate collaboration, communication, and collective responsibility. Individual sports build self-discipline, goal-setting abilities, and resilience through both victory and defeat. Physical fitness benefits are undeniable, with regular sports participation correlating with improved cardiovascular health and reduced childhood obesity rates. Moreover, sports provide structured environments for social development, teaching children to respect authority, resolve conflicts, and celebrate achievements.\n\nIn my considered opinion, competitive sports can be profoundly beneficial when grounded in child-centered principles. Adults must prioritize participation over victory, ensuring sports remain fun and developmentally appropriate. Implementing age-specific rules, emphasizing skill development over winning, and providing comprehensive coaching in sportsmanship are essential. When balanced with adequate rest and recovery, competitive sports can foster physical, emotional, and social growth that extends far beyond the playing field.',
    modelAnswerCN: '竞技体育在儿童发展中占据复杂的地位，在提供潜在好处的同时也带来了重大风险，需要教练、家长和教育工作者谨慎管理。\n\n批评者强调了儿童竞技体育的几个合理担忧。不惜一切代价取胜的心态会造成过度压力，导致焦虑、表现压力甚至倦怠。身体伤害始终是一个风险，特别是在足球或体操等高接触性运动中。过分强调竞争可能会助长不健康的比较，并削弱体育活动的内在乐趣，可能会让孩子完全远离体育。此外，获得资源和教练的机会不平等可能会加剧青少年体育参与中的社会差距。\n\n支持者强调竞技体育可以传授的变革性生活课程。团队运动培养协作、沟通和集体责任感。个人运动通过胜利和失败来培养自律、目标设定能力和韧性。身体健康益处是不可否认的，定期参加体育运动与改善心血管健康和降低儿童肥胖率相关。此外，体育为社会发展提供了结构化的环境，教导儿童尊重权威、解决冲突和庆祝成就。\n\n在我深思熟虑的观点中，当竞技体育以儿童为中心的原则为基础时，它可能会带来深远的益处。成年人必须优先考虑参与而非胜利，确保体育运动保持乐趣并适合发展。实施针对年龄的规则，强调技能发展而非获胜，并提供全面的体育精神教练至关重要。当与充足的休息和恢复相平衡时，竞技体育可以促进超越运动场的身体、情感和社会成长。',
    bandScore: 'Band 8.5',
