    topic: 'Single Parents',
    question: 'What are the advantages and disadvantages of being a single parent? Give reasons for your answer and include any relevant examples.',
    modelAnswer: 'Single parenting represents a significant shift in family structures worldwide, shaped by changing social norms and personal circumstances. While often challenging, it also offers unique opportunities for growth and connection.\n\nSingle parenting fosters profound parent-child bonds. Without a co-parent, caregivers often develop intense emotional connections with their children, characterized by mutual trust and dependency. Decision-making autonomy allows single parents to implement consistent parenting styles without compromise, creating stability for children. Many single parents report increased self-reliance and personal growth, developing resilience through navigating challenges independently.\n\nHowever, single parenting presents substantial difficulties. Financial strain is common, as one income must support an entire household. Time management becomes exceptionally demanding, with parents juggling work, childcare, and household responsibilities. Children may experience emotional challenges related to absent parents or societal stigma. Social isolation can occur when single parents struggle to maintain personal relationships alongside caregiving duties.\n\nIn conclusion, single parenting embodies both struggles and strengths. While financial and logistical challenges are significant, the emotional rewards and personal growth can be transformative. Society must provide greater support—including affordable childcare, flexible work policies, and community resources—to empower single parents. With adequate support systems, single-parent families can thrive and provide nurturing environments for children.',
    modelAnswerCN: '单亲育儿代表了全球家庭结构的重大转变，受到不断变化的社会规范和个人情况的影响。虽然常常具有挑战性，但它也提供了独特的成长和联系机会。\n\n单亲育儿培养深厚的亲子关系。没有共同父母，照顾者通常与孩子建立强烈的情感联系，以相互信任和依赖为特征。决策自主权允许单亲父母在不妥协的情况下实施一致的育儿方式，为孩子创造稳定性。许多单亲父母报告说，通过独立应对挑战，他们的自立能力和个人成长得到了提高。\n\n然而，单亲育儿也存在重大困难。经济压力很常见，因为一份收入必须支撑整个家庭。时间管理变得异常苛刻，父母要兼顾工作、育儿和家务责任。孩子可能会经历与父母缺席或社会污名相关的情感挑战。当单亲父母在照顾职责之外难以维持个人关系时，可能会发生社会孤立。\n\n总之，单亲育儿既体现了挣扎，也体现了优势。虽然经济和后勤挑战很大，但情感回报和个人成长可能是变革性的。社会必须提供更大的支持——包括负担得起的托儿服务、灵活的工作政策和社区资源——以增强单亲父母的能力。有了足够的支持系统，单亲家庭可以茁壮成长，并为孩子提供养育环境。',
    bandScore: 'Band 8.5',
    keywords: ['single parent', 'family', 'children', 'responsibility', 'support', 'resilience']
