    question: 'What are the advantages and disadvantages of e-books compared to traditional printed books?',
    modelAnswer: 'The digital revolution has sparked a profound transformation in reading habits, with e-books emerging as a powerful alternative to traditional printed books while maintaining distinct advantages and limitations.\n\nE-books offer compelling benefits rooted in digital convenience. Portability stands out—readers can carry entire libraries on lightweight devices, ideal for travel or commuting. Adjustable font sizes, text-to-speech functionality, and customizable backgrounds enhance accessibility for readers with visual impairments or reading difficulties. E-books are often more affordable than printed versions, with many classic works available for free or at minimal cost. Environmentally, e-books reduce paper consumption and the carbon footprint associated with printing and shipping. Search functionality enables instant information retrieval, while digital annotations can be easily organized and shared. E-books never go out of print, preserving literary works indefinitely.\n\nTraditional printed books retain enduring appeal through sensory and tactile experiences. The physical act of turning pages, the smell of paper and ink, and the tangible weight of a book create immersive reading experiences that digital formats cannot replicate. Printed books require no technology, batteries, or internet access, ensuring reliability in any situation. Many readers find it easier to navigate physical books—skimming, bookmarking, and annotating feel more natural with pen and paper. The aesthetic appeal of beautifully designed books, with their covers, typography, and illustrations, enhances reading pleasure. Printed books also serve as tangible artifacts, carrying sentimental value and acting as decorative elements in living spaces.\n\nIn conclusion, e-books and printed books serve complementary roles in modern reading culture. E-books excel in convenience, portability, and accessibility, making them ideal for casual reading, research, and on-the-go consumption. Printed books provide superior tactile experiences, aesthetic pleasure, and reliability, suited for deep reading, study, and collection. Many readers embrace both formats, using e-books for convenience while cherishing printed books for special occasions and meaningful reading experiences. The future of reading lies not in choosing between formats but in embracing the richness of both.',
    modelAnswerCN: '数字革命引发了阅读习惯的深刻变革，电子书作为传统印刷书籍的强大替代品出现，同时保持着独特的优势和局限性。\n\n电子书提供了基于数字便利性的令人信服的好处。便携性脱颖而出——读者可以在轻便设备上携带整个图书馆，非常适合旅行或通勤。可调节的字体大小、文本转语音功能和可定制的背景增强了视障或阅读困难读者的可访问性。电子书通常比印刷版更便宜，许多经典作品可以免费或以最低成本获得。在环境方面，电子书减少纸张消耗以及与印刷和运输相关的碳足迹。搜索功能支持即时信息检索，而数字注释可以轻松组织和共享。电子书永远不会绝版，无限期保存文学作品。\n\n传统印刷书籍通过感官和触觉体验保持持久的吸引力。翻页的物理动作、纸张和墨水的气味以及书的有形重量创造了数字格式无法复制的沉浸式阅读体验。印刷书籍不需要技术、电池或互联网接入，确保在任何情况下都可靠。许多读者发现浏览实体书更容易——用钢笔和纸进行浏览、书签和注释感觉更自然。设计精美的书籍的美学吸引力，包括封面、排版和插图，增强了阅读乐趣。印刷书籍也是有形的艺术品，具有情感价值，并作为生活空间中的装饰元素。\n\n总之，电子书和印刷书籍在现代阅读文化中扮演着互补的角色。电子书在便利性、便携性和可访问性方面表现出色，非常适合休闲阅读、研究和随时随地消费。印刷书籍提供卓越的触觉体验、美学乐趣和可靠性，适合深度阅读、学习和收藏。许多读者接受两种格式，使用电子书方便，同时珍视印刷书籍用于特殊场合和有意义的阅读体验。阅读的未来不在于在格式之间做出选择，而在于拥抱两者的丰富性。',
    bandScore: 'Band 8.5',
    keywords: ['books', 'reading', 'technology', 'literature', 'digital', 'media']
